p:
Jim and Martha are standing together at the corner of a rectangular field. Jim walks diagonally across the field, while Martha gets to the same location by walking along its length and width. The field is 300 feet wide and 400 feet long. The problem is to find out how many feet less than Martha does Jim walk.The rectangular field can be represented using the following LaTeX diagram: egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) rectangle (4,3);\draw (0,0) -- (4,3);
ode at (2,1.5) {Jim};
ode at (3,0.3) {Martha};
ode at (2,-0.3) {400 feet};
ode at (-0.3,1.5) {300 feet};\end{tikzpicture}
